The negotiations had ended very quickly in the last few hours because they feared the effect of a new failure on the mood of investors.
The last time they had set was the opening of the markets this morning.
The two candidates in the U.S. presidential election, who have joined late in the negotiations, were rather favorable to the agreement, not forgetting however to express their displeasure at being forced to reach this extremity.
Democratic Senator Barack Obama was given certain provisions to reach the agreement, particularly the one that would allow homeowners to keep their domicile and that on the salary of the leaders of the surviving companies by the state.
“When taxpayers are asked to take extraordinary action because of the irresponsibility of some, they are not to be congratulated.
