Listening to music at high volume for a long period of time using portable music devices such as Mp3 players can cause permanent hearing injuries.
This is what the European Commission says, which in a statement released in Brussels cites the opinion of the Scientific Commission on Emerging and Recently Identified Health Risk (Csseri) of the EU, published today.
“From this scientific opinion, it emerges that 5-10% of those who, for a period of at least 5 years, listen to music with portable musical devices weekly for more than an hour a day having the device at high volume risk a permanent loss of hearing capacity.”
