It is the day of the launch of OpenOffice.org 3.0, the open source suite of personal productivity that aims to attract more and more users, from home to office to public administration professionals, as a free alternative to the well-known Microsoft Office.
After almost a year of work on the part of the volunteer developers, whose backs are monitored by SUN Microsystem, the new Open Office is shown to the public with several novelties: to the welcome screen and the less rude magazine interface, more consistent ones are added, such as compatibility for the Apple Mac OS X operating system and support for the new format ODF (Open Document Format) 1.2, the latest ISO standard version.
Attention also to the multi-function with the Office 2007 suite, Open Office is able to open documents with the new Microsoft extension (.docx, .xlsx, .pptx).
